data.meta_description: "Recollections of the Early History of Northern Wisconsin," by Henry S. Baird, recounts Baird's (1800-1875) early years in northern Wisconsin. Baird came to Green Bay in 1824, became the first professional lawyer to practice in Wisconsin, was prominent in Indian affairs, and eventually played an integral part in territorial politics. He describes the landscape, early settlers and town affairs, and the Indians in the area. (25 pages)
